The paper focuses on evaluating the performance of human-AI teams in a cooperative game involving a visual conversational agent. This involves aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.HC, followed by cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.LG.
